Nigerian States Agree to Ending Petrol Subsidy, ThisDay Says

-- B y   E m e l e   O n u
-- 
2011-10-08T08:44:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-08/nigerian-states-agree-to-ending-petrol-subsidy-thisday-says.html
Nigeria ’s federal government and the
country’s 36 individual states agreed yesterday to stop
subsidizing petroleum products and to channel the money saved to
welfare programs, the Lagos-based ThisDay newspaper reported,
citing Chibuike Amaechi, the chairman of the Nigerian Governors’
Forum and Governor of Rivers State in the Niger Delta region.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emele Onu in Johannesburg at 
 eonu1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
